Basic Commands of Linux
-----------------------
    #cd to change the directory.

    #ls used to list directories and files.

    #mkdir to create a directory.

    #rmdir to remove a directory.

    #touch used to create an empty file.

    #date to display current.

    #cal to display a calendar.

    #cat to display content of file directly to terminal.

    #whoami display username currently log in
tested

